		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Single Euro Payments Area</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:322px;"><a href="/wiki/File:SEPA.PNG" class="image" title="The Single Euro Payments Area and its 32 member states"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/16/SEPA.PNG/320px-SEPA.PNG" width="320" height="300" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:SEPA.PNG" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
The Single Euro Payments Area and its 32 member states</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><b>The Single Euro Payments Area (SEPA)</b> initiative for the <a href="/wiki/Europe" title="Europe">European</a> financial <a href="/wiki/Infrastructure" title="Infrastructure">infrastructure</a> involves the creation of a zone for the <a href="/wiki/Euro" title="Euro">euro</a> in which all electronic payments are considered domestic, and where a difference between national and intra-European cross border payments does not exist. The project aims to improve the efficiency of cross border payments and turn the fragmented national markets for euro payments into a single domestic one: SEPA will enable customers to make cashless euro payments to anyone located anywhere in the area using only a single bank account and a single set of payment instruments.<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> The project includes the development of common <a href="/wiki/Financial_instruments" title="Financial instruments" class="mw-redirect">financial instruments</a>, standards, procedures, and infrastructure to enable <a href="/wiki/Economies_of_scale" title="Economies of scale" class="mw-redirect">economies of scale</a>. This should in turn reduce the overall cost to the European economy of moving capital around the region (estimated today as 2%-3% of total GDP).<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1" title=""><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
